Newhaven Harbour to Lewes Train Travel Guide

Travelling by train from Newhaven Harbour to Lewes provides passengers with a convenient and efficient way to commute or explore, ensuring that they arrive on time. For a smooth travel experience, please check out our Train Journey Planner.

Plan Your Train Journey

The train from Newhaven Harbour to Lewes takes approximately 11m. There are an average of 31 trains per day running from Newhaven Harbour to Lewes. The first train departs at 08:03, while the last train leaves at 23:03. For more details, please refer to our Train Journey Planner and Timetable.

Book Cheap Train Tickets

Train tickets from Newhaven Harbour to Lewes are available with Split Ticket and Advance tickets. The average fare is around £3.50, while the cheapest fare is £3.50*. Besides, you can book cheap tickets on off-peak time, which usually begin at 09:30.(Intercity Off-Peak times: Monday to Friday from 09:30 to 16:00, and after 19:00) . Accurate ticket prices vary depending on the time of day, route, and class selected.

Train Stations

You can choose to start from Brighton,Brighton,London,London Victoria,Falmer,Eastbourne,London Road (Brighton),or Gatwick Airport Station to Lewes by train.
